body_html:
@caisq That's mysterious, because there's no platform-specific code in that test (as far as I can tell). To unblock the process while I investigate, can you add the following line:

      "${tensorflow_source_dir}/tensorflow/contrib/data/python/kernel_tests/dataset_constructor_op_test.py"

...to the list of tests to disable on Windows, here:

https://github.com/av8ramit/tensorflow/blob/5abe2a643c591f91d73abd53502ab2ac344298e6/tensorflow/contrib/cmake/tf_tests.cmake#L217

body:
@caisq That's mysterious, because there's no platform-specific code in that test (as far as I can tell). To unblock the process while I investigate, can you add the following line:

```
      "${tensorflow_source_dir}/tensorflow/contrib/data/python/kernel_tests/dataset_constructor_op_test.py"
```

...to the list of tests to disable on Windows, here:

https://github.com/av8ramit/tensorflow/blob/5abe2a643c591f91d73abd53502ab2ac344298e6/tensorflow/contrib/cmake/tf_tests.cmake#L217
